      <category><![CDATA[Selling Online]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.alisonrothwell.com/?p=1089</guid>
      <description>In today’s interview series, we talk with Laura Morris of RentABuggy&amp;#8230; My name is Laura Morris and I am a single mother to my beautiful daughter, Ashleigh, who is 4 years old. I founded my business www.rentabuggy.co.uk in 2008 and I am just coming into my second year. Rentabuggy allows families to ease cash flow [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/social-media-marketing/Social_Media_Marketing-My_Site_in_Cyperspace-_Laura_Morris.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p>
<p><em><strong>In today’s interview series, we talk with Laura Morris of RentABuggy&#8230;</strong></em></p>
<p><strong><em> </em></strong></p>
<p><strong><em> </em></strong></p>
<p><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-1312" style="margin-left: 5px; margin-right: 5px;" title="Laura Morris" src="http://www.onlinemarketingvillage.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/meandash-300x225.jpg" alt="meandash 300x225 My Site in Cyperspace: Laura Morris" width="176" height="132" />My name is Laura Morris and I am a single mother to my beautiful daughter, Ashleigh, who is 4 years old. I founded my business <a href="http://www.rentabuggy.co.uk/" target="_blank">www.rentabuggy.co.uk</a> in 2008 and I am just coming into my second year. Rentabuggy allows families to ease cash flow and rent top selling pushchairs on a monthly basis. We also provide holiday rentals Nationwide including travel cots, highchairs, sterilisers and much more. I am also Co-Founder of <a href="http://www.networkingmummies.com/" target="_blank">www.networkingmummies.com</a> that was started in February 2009 with my business partner Joanne Dewberry of <a href="http://www.charliemoos.co.uk/" target="_blank">www.charliemoos.co.uk</a>. We provide free events with no membership fees for women in Business. We also do further events throughout the year including exhibitions, workshops and much more.</p>
<p><em> <strong>Why I started selling online&#8230;</strong></em></p>
<p><strong><em> </em></strong></p>
<p>As soon as I had the idea for Rentabuggy, I knew it was an online business. I didn’t even contemplate having premises as I knew where my target market was.</p>
<p><strong><em>What has been my biggest online marketing challenge&#8230;</em></strong></p>
<p><strong><em> </em></strong></p>
<p>The way that the world is moving is all about Social Networking and to the massive extent of using this for your business. It is a new way of ‘word of mouth’ advertising and it took me a while to get my head around how it would work for me and my businesses. However, only this week I actually held a Networking Mummies workshop for 17 people on how to use Social Networking to market their businesses!</p>
<p><strong><em> </em></strong></p>
<p><strong><em>What do I like best about my website&#8230;</em></strong></p>
<p>I like that it is sleek and simple and I like my logo.</p>
<p><strong><em>My top online marketing tip&#8230;</em></strong></p>
<p><strong><em> </em></strong></p>
<p>Use a blog. I have only recently within the past six months started using a blog but it is great to let my customers know of any news, competitions and offers and not only that but by using correct keywords etc, I can increase my Google rankings.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rentabuggy.co.uk/" target="_blank">www.rentabuggy.co.uk</a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.networkingmummies.com/" target="_blank">www.networkingmummies.com</a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.mumtomumpreneur.co.uk/" target="_blank">www.mumtomumpreneur.co.uk</a></p>

]]></content:encoded>
