      <description><![CDATA[We were tagged by Antonia over at Family Friendly Working, to say seven things you didn&#8217;t know about us, so here goes! Ali&#8217;s 7 Things&#8230; 1. I love handbags with a passion. You will know I&#8217;ve made it when I sport a Chanel black 2.55 as my arm candy. 2. The last time I sang [...]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p>
<p>We were tagged by Antonia over at <a title="family friendly working" href="www.familyfriendlyworking.co.uk/2010/04/16/7-things-you-didnt-know-about-me/" target="_blank">Family Friendly Working</a>, to say seven things you didn&#8217;t know about us, so here goes!</p>
<p><strong>Ali&#8217;s 7 Things&#8230;</strong></p>
<p>1. I love handbags with a passion. You will know I&#8217;ve made it when I sport a Chanel black 2.55 as my arm candy.</p>
<p>2. The last time I sang in public was when I was 18 and played Mrs Peachum in The Threepenny Opera.</p>
<p>3. I&#8217;ve had a crush on Harrison Ford for 33 years&#8230;</p>
<p>4. I suffered from secondary infertility.</p>
<p>5. I&#8217;m a big Sci-fi fan.</p>
<p>6. I have all of Nigel Slater&#8217;s recipe books and I hold him responsible for my current punishing diet.</p>
<p>7. I was once a very political animal.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;"><img src="http://www.selfemployedmum.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/skitched-20100422-114548.jpg" width="360" height="270" alt="skitched 20100422 114548 7 Things You Didn’t Know About Us – Harrison Ford love, celebrity turn downs, & a pic with Bob Marley"  title="7 Things You Didn’t Know About Us – Harrison Ford love, celebrity turn downs, & a pic with Bob Marley" /></span></strong></p>
<p><strong>Natalie&#8217;s 7 Things&#8230;</strong></p>
<p>1. I was brought up in Dublin so I have a mixed accent. When I started blogging and was anonymous, people assumed I was fair skinned with red hair&#8230;</p>
<p>2. I&#8217;ve been doing acupuncture for 4 years as it helped me to recover from an immune system disease, Sarcoidosis.</p>
<p>3. I have about 100 pairs of shoes although most have been neglected since I had kids&#8230;</p>
<p>4. I was asked by a very famous rapper to go back to his hotel room with him and his entourage but I declined telling him that &#8216;group activities&#8217; aren&#8217;t my thang&#8230;</p>
<p>5. I watch at least one episode of Sex and the City each week.</p>
<p>6. I have an early baby picture of me being held by Bob Marley (as shown).</p>
<p>7. I&#8217;ve lost a Mulberry handbag in my attic. I keep meaning to do a clearout&#8230;</p>

]]></content:encoded>
