      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p>
<p><a href="http://www.alisonrothwell.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/Samorost-21.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-555  alignleft" title="Samorost-2" src="http://www.alisonrothwell.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/Samorost-21.jpg" alt="Samorost 21 Shirkers Secrets: Samorost" width="120" height="90" /></a>Woo! It&#8217;s Friday afternoon and we have another downtime dirty secret to share with you <img src='http://www.alisonrothwell.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif' alt="icon wink Shirkers Secrets: Samorost" class='wp-smiley' title="Shirkers Secrets: Samorost" /> </p>
<p>This week we&#8217;re introducing you to Samorost.</p>
<p>Samorost is an adventure game created by Czech game designer Jakub Dvorsky and published by Amanita Designs. It&#8217;s a point and click flash game where the game&#8217;s main charecter, a gnome-like creature, battles to save his planet from collision with a spaceship. In the sequel, Samorost 2, the gnome&#8217;s task is to rescue his dog, which has been kidnapped by aliens.</p>
<p>The music and sound effects are superb and the music can be downloaded from Itunes.</p>
<p><a title="Samorost" href="http://amanita-design.net/samorost-1/" target="_blank"><strong>Samorost</strong></a> can be downloaded for FREE while the first part of <strong><a title="Samorost 2" href="http://amanita-design.net/samorost-2/" target="_blank">Samorost 2</a> </strong>can be played online for free with a full edition with five more levels costing just $5.00</p>
